<br />
	&quot;Fighting <a href="javascript:card_browser(400)">Furok</a>s 1.4&quot;<br />
	By: ErnieIII   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Okay here we go!<br />
<br />
*****General strategy for magi*****<br />
<br />
 TILLER - One of narooms best set up magi.  First turn I try to go first if possible but either way I i ditch the weeblit for 2 cards, play the Vortex of knowlege. and ditch any creatures that arent needed. Play a couple creatures to keep tiller alive and them from there depending on what your opponent plays you decide whether your going to be defensive with tiller ar more aggressive. if playing O&#39;qua your gonna be aggresive to take her out as soon as possible same with underneath. if your playing against KT i would be more defensive since i probable want to save my good cards for my powerful magi where they can be useful. Ditch all the firds since you can get them back by playing a furok.<br />
<br />
	*Cards to save with Tiller* <br />
		Furok x1- for sperri<br />
		Baby Furok x3 - For sperri<br />
		Fird stone - Sperri<br />
		Wasperine Stalker - Make use of Yakis Double strike power<br />
		Warriors boots x As many as possible for yaki and sperri<br />
		Forest hyren (he doesnt really need to be saved but hes good with yaki since its big)<br />
<br />
YAKI - Hes a very powerful magi and has a decent starting energy.  Most of the time if tiller had time to draw some cards yaki can flip kill. He does this by playing wasperine stalkers to take all energy off their magi and then somehow clearing the board with either,Ormagon,thunderquake,Wasperines, or a boots in creature. or he can play a creature attack with it and then impact it. this works good with forest hyren + weebo combos. Play ember hyren and attack a bunch of times to gain him lots of energy ( Who wouldnt want free energy!) A lot of the time yaki can take out two magi by flip killing and then just playing him out normal.<br />
<br />
	*Cards to save with Tiller*<br />
		Furok x2<br />
		Baby furok x3 ( by this time you might not have all 3 but try to)<br />
 		Fird Stone <br />
		Warriors boots - as many as you could save.<br />
		yakis Gauntlets - Furok power!!<br />
<br />
SPERRI- My favorite magi, she is underestimated by too many people but shes a beast!  Heres where all the fun begins.  First you want to check to see if you can  flip kill ( especially if ther eon there 3rd Magi) One way to do this is play fird stone,yakis gauntlets, some warriors boots. use the gauntlets so you can attack twice now. Play some furoks at 6 energy! becasue of sperri. Attack with them and gain energy back on sperri. sometimes that alone will kill them, Add stuff like Thunderquake,energy band,impact,Bythans gift, wasperine stalker...theres so many different ways to get around thir creatures to eliminate their magi. Or play defensive and then  use spells to take them out. Cna you imagine playing a fird stone with 3, 4energy baby furoks that cost me 6 Energy!<br />
<br />
***** Card Breakdown*****<br />
<br />
3 Furok - USe for sperri<br />
3 Baby furok- Use for sperri<br />
3 Wasperine - Very good card , built in warriors boots!<br />
2 Wasperine Stalker - This creature is so good with yaki or any other magi.<br />
2 Ember hyren - Free energy + decent power and a soild 5 energy creature<br />
2 Flame rudwot - These things are crazy, Versatile too<br />
2 Fird- Ditch with tiller and you wont hve to worry about getting them back to play with sperri!<br />
2 Giant Carillion - Discard<br />
2 Weebo- Use with forest hryen or giant carillion or just play it to keep you alive<br />
1 Forest hyren - I dotn like paying a lot of energy for creatures thats why im playing only one, but its very good<br />
1 Ormagon - Clears the board ( has one me so many games)<br />
<br />
2 Bythans Gift - Energy gain<br />
2 Thunderquake- Discard<br />
2 Impact- Energy removal<br />
1 Beam of light- Relics,creature,spell discard<br />
1 Vortex of knowledge - Draw with tiller<br />
<br />
3 Warriors boots- ....Kinda obvious<br />
2 Rayjes belt- Staple card for most decks, Disables the using of almost any power<br />
2 Energy Band- Gives you a boost<br />
